## Functional Requirements

**FR-001**: System MUST accept both email addresses and usernames in the email/username field

**FR-002**: System MUST enforce password complexity requirements (min 8 chars, uppercase, lowercase, number, special char)

**FR-003**: System MUST validate all inputs client-side before submitting to API

**FR-004**: System MUST send credentials securely to `POST /api/v1/auth/signin` endpoint

**FR-005**: System MUST store refresh token in HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookie

**FR-006**: System MUST store access token in memory (not localStorage/sessionStorage)

**FR-007**: System MUST redirect authenticated users to `/dashboard` on successful sign-in

**FR-008**: System MUST display appropriate error messages for all failure scenarios

**FR-009**: System MUST implement rate limiting (max 5 failed attempts per 15 minutes)

**FR-010**: System MUST lock account temporarily after 5 failed attempts

**FR-011**: System MUST send email notification on account lockout

**FR-012**: System MUST log all authentication attempts (success/failure) for security monitoring

**FR-013**: System MUST redirect unauthenticated users to `/signin` when accessing protected routes

**FR-014**: System MUST redirect already authenticated users to `/dashboard` when accessing `/signin`

**FR-015**: System MUST provide show/hide password toggle functionality

**FR-016**: System MUST auto-trim whitespace from email/username and password before validation

**FR-017**: System MUST use generic error message "Invalid email or password" for authentication failures (security)

**FR-018**: System MUST implement silent token refresh 5 minutes before access token expiry

**FR-019**: System MUST invalidate all tokens on logout

**FR-020**: System MUST support up to 5 concurrent active sessions per user

*Assumptions made:*

- **A-001**: User accounts are pre-created via admin or separate registration flow
- **A-002**: Email verification is handled separately (not part of this sign-in flow)
- **A-003**: OAuth applications (Google, Microsoft) configured separately (out of scope)
- **A-004**: SSO provider configuration managed via admin panel (out of scope)
- **A-005**: Password reset flow implemented as separate feature
- **A-006**: Backend API for authentication is implemented and available
- **A-007**: SMTP/email service configured for sending lockout notifications

---

## Success Criteria

**SC-001**: Users can successfully sign in using email/password in under 5 seconds (from button click to dashboard load)

**SC-002**: 95% of users successfully complete sign-in on first attempt (no validation errors)

**SC-003**: Authentication API maintains 99.9% uptime with <500ms response time (p95)

**SC-004**: Zero critical or high security vulnerabilities in authentication flow (per security audit)

**SC-005**: WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance verified via automated (axe, Lighthouse) and manual testing

**SC-006**: User satisfaction rating for sign-in experience is 4.5/5 or higher (post-launch survey)

**SC-007**: Account lockout mechanism prevents >99% of brute-force attacks in penetration testing

**SC-008**: <1% of sign-in attempts result in support tickets (usability metric)

---

## Out of Scope (Separate User Stories)

- Google OAuth authentication flow
- Microsoft OAuth authentication flow
- SSO/SAML authentication flow
- Password reset / forgot password flow
- New user registration / sign-up flow
- Email verification flow
- Multi-factor authentication (MFA)
- "Remember me" checkbox functionality
- Social account linking (connect Google/Microsoft to existing account)
- Session management UI (view active sessions, sign out from all)
- Account recovery flow

